The Herald Freedom Mupanedemo Midlands Bureau A 39-year-old popular Gweru bouncer was found hanging in a bush following an argument with his wife. Midlands provincial police spokesperson, Inspector Emmanuel Mahoko said the deceased, Shoenyann Caterlang Bones, was found hanging on a tree in the early hours of yesterday in a bush near the Travellers Rest plot along the Gweru-Chiwundura road. He used to work at a local upmarket nightclub, Pablos. “It was reported that the deceased, Shoenyann Caterlang Bones had a misunderstanding with his wife and later left home to an unknown destination. “His body was then found hanging from a tree some 30m away from their home early yesterday,” said Insp Mahoko